headline: Gemini Stock Starts Trading Today. It Could Be Another Win for the Winklevoss Twins.
summary: Gemini Space Station, the crypto brokerage firm that actually is run by twins Cameron and Tyler Winklevoss, announced the pricing for its initial public offering after the market closed Thursday and will begin trading on the Nasdaq under the ticker symbol GEMI on Friday.  The IPO was priced at $28 a share, above the range.  At that price range, Gemini would have a market valuation of $3.3 billion.
